## Frontend environment variables
## Copy to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and adjust as needed.

## Enable API-backed mode (recommended for production deploys)
## - If omitted in a production build, the app defaults to `true`.
VITE_USE_BACKEND_API=true

## Frontend base URL for QR links (optional)
VITE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5173

## API base used by the frontend fetch() calls
## - Local dev (recommended): keep this as `/api/v1` and use the Vite proxy below.
## - Production: you can omit this; the app will default to `${VITE_SUPABASE_URL}/functions/v1/server/api/v1`.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

## Vite dev proxy target for `/api/v1/*` -> `${target}/functions/v1/server/api/v1/*`
## If you run `supabase start`, the default local API gateway is `http://localhost:54321`.
VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:54321

## Optional: enable Supabase social login
## - Required for Google/Facebook OAuth flows.
## - Can be used together with backend API mode.
VITE_ENABLE_SUPABASE_AUTH=false
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

## Optional: force a specific public site origin for auth redirects (email/OAuth)
## Example: https://your-site.netlify.app
VITE_SITE_URL=

## Optional: frontend password policy (UI validation)
VITE_AUTH_PASSWORD_MIN_LENGTH=6

## Admin signup code
## - Set `ADMIN_SIGNUP_CODE` only in the backend function environment.
## - Do not expose the admin signup code through `VITE_` variables.
